text: Aaron B. Rollins (1818 - December 4, 1878) was a politician connected to the Tammany Hall political machine. He served in New York's legislature in 1852. He was later elected coroner for New York City from 1867 to 1870. ==Biography== Rollins was born in 1818. He died on December 4, 1878 at the Union-Place Hotel in Manhattan. ==References== Category:Democratic Party (United States) politicians Category:Politicians from New York (state) Category:1818 births Category:People from New York City Category:1878 deaths
